{"id":43872,"date":"2025-07-03T19:44:01","date_gmt":"2025-07-03T15:44:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=43872"},"modified":"2025-07-05T14:28:47","modified_gmt":"2025-07-05T10:28:47","slug":"noah-forgive-my-people","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/07\/03\/noah-forgive-my-people\/","title":{"rendered":"Nuh on Patience: Forgive my people for they do not know"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>\u2018Ubayd ibn \u2018Umayr reported: They used to beat and strangle Noah, upon him be peace, until he fainted. When he woke up, Noah said, \u201cO Allah, forgive my people for they do not know.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Tafsi\u0304r Ibn Abi\u0304 H\u0323a\u0304tim 7:59<\/p>\n<p>Al-Qadi \u2018Iyad commented, \u201cA similar statement was narrated from our Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, on the day of Uhud. In this is their forbearance, patience, and compassion for their peoples and nations, that despite what they did to them and how they hurt them, they prayed for their forgiveness and excused them for their ignorance, as they had only been given a little knowledge.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Ikma\u0304l al-Mu\u2019lim bi-Fawa\u0304\u2019id Muslim 6\/164<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u062b\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0628\u064e\u0644\u064e\u063a\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u064a\u064e\u0628\u0652\u0637\u0650\u0634\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u064a\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0646\u064f\u0648\u062d\u064b\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064e\u0651\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064f \u064